According to statistics, between 30 and 75 % of car drivers charged with more than once intoxication will once again sit behind the wheel in this state.
Alcolock should prevent this because it is a system attached to a vehicle that measures the level of alcohol in the breathed air and prevents the car from starting if the driver does not breathe before or if it is recorded higher than the permitted alcohol concentration.
Its price exceeds 1,000 euros and would have to be paid by the culprit himself.
The study carried out in this sense in the USA in 2007 showed that, in the case of vehicles equipped with this equipment, offences decreased by 65 % during the first year since the introduction.
In Spain, the possibility of saving 115 people every year is the result.
The measure is limited to administrative sanctions for two reasons: to deal with this behaviour before it leads to a criminal offence.
And in order to help put it in place, as legislation can be implemented in the usual way, however, the necessary adjustment of criminal provisions requires amendment of the law.
The equipment is not yet available on the Spanish market in any sales version, although some industrial vehicles and public service vehicles have already been installed with experience.
